Project.Title: Analyze key proteins in Syntrophus aciditrophicus
Project.Description: Pure cultures of S. aciditrophicus grown in 250 ml of 20 mM crotonate medium in 500-ml Schott bottles were used for proteomic analysis after 2-dimensional (2-D) PAGE.

PubMed.PubMedInfo: James KL, Kung JW, Crable BR, Mouttaki H, Sieber JR, Nguyen HH, Yang Y, Xie Y, Erde J, Wofford NQ, Karr EA, Loo JA, Ogorzalek Loo RR, Gunsalus RP, McInerney MJ Syntrophus aciditrophicus uses the same enzymes in a reversible manner to degrade and synthesize aromatic and alicyclic acids. Environ Microbiol. 2019 Mar 20;
